          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1586950310404-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has browned, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>mirin</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 4-5 min further or until fragrant and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>fragrant Japanese-style pork</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1586950340954-x200.jpg",
